This repository bundles third-party code under separate licenses. You are
responsible for complying with those licenses when you redistribute or
deploy birdybird.

1. Ocean3.js / Ocean4.js — CC BY-NC-SA 3.0 (non-commercial)
   Files: src/vendor/Ocean3.js, src/vendor/Ocean4.js
   Authors: Phil Crowther, Attila Schroeder (WebGPU port). Based on earlier
   work by David Li, Aleksandr Albert, and Jérémy Bouny.
   License: Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 3.0
   Unported — https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/

   Because these files are active by default in the rendered water surface,
   deployments of birdybird that keep them compiled in inherit the NC
   ("NonCommercial") restriction: you may not use the deployed work for
   commercial purposes without replacing the Ocean* modules with the
   included Gerstner-wave fallback (see `src/world/WaterPlane.js`
   `_createGerstnerWater` / `_createWebGPUWater`), which is MIT-licensed
   along with the rest of this repo.

2. RedReddingtonForest.js / RedReddingtonForestNode.js — MIT
   Files: src/vendor/RedReddingtonForest.js, src/vendor/RedReddingtonForestNode.js
   Author: red-reddington (https://codepen.io/the-red-reddington)
   Ported and adapted with permission. MIT-compatible with the rest of
   this repo.

3. Stork 3D model — community asset
   File: public/models/Stork.glb
   Provenance: free community glTF asset; treat as CC0-equivalent for
   this project. Replace with your own asset if stricter provenance is
   required.

4. Terrain and building textures — CC0
   Source: Poly Haven (https://polyhaven.com)

5. Three.js — MIT (https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js)
   lil-gui — MIT (https://github.com/georgealways/lil-gui)
   MediaPipe Tasks Vision — Apache 2.0
     (https://github.com/google/mediapipe)

Attribution for all of the above is carried in the live Credits overlay
(click "Credits" in the top bar) at runtime.
